sentences.content: The reset button clears fill-in prompt fields and removes strikethroughs from the responses.
Otherwise, the reset button is disabled.
The tagging button toggles between showing and hiding tags for prompts and responses.
The prompts are tagged below the word.
The responses are labeled either parenthetically or group headings.
The progression order button toggles between showing and hiding the slider that adjusts the order of responses and reveal of prompt fill-ins.
The slider allows the order change progressively from easy to difficult:
Fill-in field within each prompt is shown.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed in order.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed alphabetically.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed randomly.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are hidden.
